 RED BOOK n. 1. Informal name for one of the three standard references on
PostScript; the others are known as the GREEN BOOK and BLUE BOOK. 2. Any of
the 1984 standards issued by the CCIT 8th plenary assembly. They change color
each review cycle (1988 was BLUE BOOK, 1992 will be GREEN BOOK). These
include, among other things, the X.400 email spec and the Group 1 through 4
fax standards. see also GREEN BOOK, BLUE BOOK, PURPLE BOOK, SILVER BOOK,
ORANGE BOOK, WHITE BOOK, PINK-SHIRT BOOK, DRAGON BOOK.